re stable platoon operation as well as maintain a constant desired time gap\nfor any combined powertrain delays and lags over 0.2 sec. These findings\ndemonstrate the potential of the asymmetric LBCM in improving platoon\noperational efficiency and stability of an automated truck platoon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Dec 2021 12:52:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Apr 2023 00:27:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-14"}
